body.description: Looking for a refreshing aluminum free deodorant? Try Dove 0% Aluminum Cucumber and Green Tea Deodorant. This aluminum free deodorant for women contains a gentle, moisturizing formula that leaves your skin feeling soft and smooth. Dove Cucumber and Green Tea Deodorant offers 24 hours of odor protection for all-day freshness. With Dove ¼ moisturizers, 0% aluminum, and 0% alcohol (ethanol) formula, this deodorant provides great underarm care with a crisp, refreshing scent. You’ll notice visibly soft and smooth underarms after just a few uses. What is the difference between deodorant and antiperspirant? Both Dove antiperspirant and Dove deodorant keep you feeling fresh and protected from odor all day long. If you need something to keep you feeling fresh, choose an aluminum free deodorant stick. Our Dove 0% Deodorant gives you up to 24 hours of odor protection. With a crisp cucumber and green tea scent, this uplifting aluminum free deodorant adds an extra burst of freshness to your routine. For more protection, use a Dove antiperspirant for women. At Dove, our vision is of a world where beauty is a source of confidence, and not anxiety. So, we are on a mission to help the next generation of women develop a positive relationship with the way they look – helping them raise their self-esteem and realize their full potential.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 17, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Dove is the best aluminum free deoderant I've tried!
reviews.reviewText: I've tried many aluminum-free deodorants and for the most part, they don't work very well but there are a few exceptions. Here are the ones I've tried and how I liked them in rank order:Winners - These work great for body odor:#1 - Dove - winner by a long shot - works and applies like regular deodorant. All-weather long-lasting protection. This is so good that I can hardly believe it's aluminum-free. Fairly priced too.#2 - Lume - works very well but, applies like a sticky lotion. It's also pretty pricy.#3 - Crystal Mineral Deodorant Stone - This one always made me nervous because it never really applied and product to my skin. It worked well for quite a while and then seemed to stop. Not sure it the minerals in the stone were depleted or if it just stopped working for me. More testing would be required with a new stick.Medium - Will do in a pinch - Works moderately well on body odor, but not as well as a regular deodorant. I'm hesitant to use these during the summer.#3 - UnderArmed - Seems to work moderately well. A little waxy in texture but otherwise applies like normal deodorant.#4 - Schmidt's Natural Deodorant - comes in a 2 oz jar that is applied like lotion - didn't care for application and only works moderately well on body odor.#5 - Jason - applies like normal deodorant but doesn't really do the job on body odor for very long.SUCKS - Waste of money and doesn't work at all#6 Secret - Applies like normal deodorant but has almost no impact on body odor. I was stinky by the end of a cool day after working in an air-conditioned office and only walking from the office to my car (10 feet from the front door). I can't imagine using this at the gym or during the summer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Reliable Aluminum-Free Deodorant
reviews.reviewText: I've been using Dove's Aluminum-Free Deodorant in the Coconut and Pink Jasmine scent, and it's been a reliable choice for me. Here's a straightforward review:Pros:- Odor Protection: This deodorant offers effective 24-hour odor protection, even on busy days.- Scent: The coconut and pink jasmine scent is pleasant without being overwhelming.- Non-Sticky: It goes on smoothly, dries quickly, and doesn't leave a sticky residue.- Skin-Friendly: It's gentle on sensitive skin and hasn't caused any irritation.One minor issue:- Cap: The cap can be a bit tricky to put back on securely.Overall, if you're looking for an aluminum-free deodorant that does its job well and has a nice scent, this Dove product is worth considering.

reviews.reviewText: Wonderful scent & good price point ! Decades ago , the only link to Alzheimer's was ALUMINUM ! AND things we put into our armpits go quickly into our bloodstreams !
